    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="655"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d655">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/10833.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Solicitor
                            <persName type="to">Folk</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 31, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">To the Solicitor</hi>: Replying to your inquiry as to when
                    Victoriano Huerta became Dictator of Mexico; I have consulted with President
                    Wilson, and find that he regards October 10th, 1913, as the date upon which
                    Victoriano Huerta became Dictator of Mexico, that being the date on which he
                    suspended the Constitution; assumed the power and authority delegated to other
                    officials; dissolved Congress, and caused a large number of the members of the
                    Mexican Congress to be imprisoned. From and after that date Victoriano Huerta
                    has been Dictator in the sense of the announcement of the President of the
                    United States that he will not recognize as legal or binding anything done by
                    Huerta since he became Dictator.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
